Description: Fragment of plaster jar-sealing; the outer convex surface bears four impressions of a seal engraved with prenomen and epithet of Psamtek II; the inner concave surface is irregular and shows several traces of negative impressions of straw strings.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Tell Dafana, "Qasr", east annex (G), chamber 29
Bibliographic references: Hall 1913 / Catalogue of Egyptian scarabs, etc. in the British Museum (2785, p. 291)
Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 51 § 49, p. 58, 59 § 57, p. 72 § 69, p. 109, pl. xxxvi, 3)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.68, p.182, pl.24, p.211)
Condition: incomplete, broken in three fragments rejoined
